  '<h2 id="threat-catalog">Threat catalog <a class="anchor" href="#threat-catalog">#</a></h2>',
  '<ul>',
  '<li><strong>Path traversal</strong> — <code>..</code>, <code>../</code>, <code>..\\</code>, percent-encoded <code>%2e%2e</code>, double-encoded <code>%252e%252e</code>, UTF-8 overlong <code>0xC0 0xAE</code> for dot and <code>0xC0 0xAF</code> for slash. Refused regardless of profile (CWE-22 / CWE-23).</li>',
  '<li><strong>Null-byte truncation</strong> — <code>file.txt\\x00.exe</code>. C-shaped APIs end the string at null; validation sees <code>.txt</code> while the OS sees <code>.exe</code>. Refused.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Windows reserved device names</strong> — CON / PRN / AUX / NUL / COM1-9 / LPT1-9 / CLOCK$ / CONFIG$. Even with extensions (<code>CON.txt</code> collides with the device). Case-insensitive match.</li>',
  '<li><strong>NTFS alternate data streams</strong> — <code>file.txt:hidden.exe</code> stream syntax.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Leading/trailing whitespace + trailing dots</strong> — Windows silently strips them, so <code>secret.txt</code> + leading space saves as <code>secret.txt</code> (collision risk).</li>',
  '<li><strong>Unicode bidi / RTLO</strong> — CVE-2021-42574 in filename context; the Memento-RTLO toolkit weaponizes this. <code>Photo01By‮gpj.SCR</code> displays as <code>Photo01ByRCS.jpg</code>; OS opens <code>.SCR</code>.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Zero-width / homoglyph chars</strong> — used to hide the real extension or spoof another filename.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Reserved characters</strong> — Windows: <code>&lt; &gt; : " | ? *</code> plus C0 controls.</li>',
  '<li><strong>UNC paths</strong> — <code>\\\\server\\share\\file</code>. Refused (network-path resolution outside local-file scope).</li>',
  '<li><strong>Path separators in leaf</strong> — <code>file/with/slashes</code> and <code>\\\\</code> variants. Strict refuses; permissive opts in to multi-component paths.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Length caps</strong> — Windows MAX_PATH 260, NTFS 32767, ext4 255 bytes per component. strict 64-byte leaf cap; balanced/permissive 255.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Multi-dot policy</strong> — strict requires single dot (rejects <code>archive.tar.gz</code>); balanced + permissive allow.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Extension allowlist</strong> — operator passes <code>extensionAllowlist: [".png", ".jpg"]</code>; non-matching extensions refused. Catches double-extension bypass: <code>file.jpg.exe</code> matches <code>.exe</code> against the allowlist.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Shell-shortcut + executable extensions</strong> — .exe / .bat / .cmd / .vbs / .js / .ps1 / .lnk / .scr / .dll / .so / .dmg / .msi / etc. Strict rejects; balanced/permissive audit-only.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Overlong UTF-8</strong> — non-shortest-form encodings (RFC 3629 §3 prohibits). Detected at the Buffer level before utf8 conversion can normalize the bytes.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Single-dot leaf</strong> — name is <code>"."</code> or <code>".."</code> always refused.</li>',
  '<li><strong>Empty filename</strong> — refused.</li>',
